Political Capital: Hungarian Guard Increases State Risk
According to the Political Capital Risk Analysis Division, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, which was founded this August with the support of the "Movement for a Better Hungary", have raised the risk of Hungary and the region in several respects.
Among other things, the Institute's "Risk Warning Report" states that in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the "enhancement of existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provocating such an argument, according to the Research Institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma issue to representatives of radical political groups who have now built up their political strategy on the Roma-Hungary-comparison".
It is believed that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, favour extremities, and increase the likelihood of violent confrontations.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guard, not least thanks to the enormous attention of the local and foreign media, "have seriously damaged Hungary's image abroad, especially in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember: Since the fall of 2006, the reorganisation of radical and extremely right groups in Hungary has been constantly on the rise, so that since the summer of 2007, several "national self-defense association" organizations have been established.
"These groups are common that they define themselves as civil organisations, while openly boasting in preparing their members for defence tasks - sometimes armed - (catastrophe protection, defense, order-keeping), calling for the inadequacy of the police, the army, or the state itself," it said.
And further on: All of this happens in accordance with the method that tries to disguise various political and party-based aspirations of the population as a bourgeois initiative based on the political and party devastation of the population.
The emphasis on the civil character and the form of the association is therefore not merely to avoid legal obstacles that could arise in the course of registration in court - it is also a political strategy.
As the analysis shows, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-enhancing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring countries, as some ultra-nationalist politicians from certain neighbouring countries see in the emergence of the Hungarian Guard the confirmation of their own anti-Hungarian policies.
All of this has an impact on the political stability of the region" - it said.
From the point of view of the Research Institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not a single phenomenon in Central Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the entire region has grown.
As reported, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are similar to those of the Bulgarian National Guard, whose establishment was announced in August 2007 by the right-wing extreme Bulgarian National Union (BNU).
