The Congress agrees with the MIFID Directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
At the same time as parliamentary drafting, which ended today with the Senate Congress decision on the additional/amendment requests relating to the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of enabling the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
