Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on different factors, including age, gender, date of creation of the driver's licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we're dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which shall determine that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and shall, in return, be obliged to present the corresponding amount of compensation in the event of a loss or injury.
The insurance premium is the price of insurance consisting of several factors, including age, sex, date of creation of the driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also payable in the event of a higher risk of accident.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since, according to statistical data, they tend to have fewer accidents than single persons, even after the company has been convinced.
The benefit to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting the premium, insurance must take into account a whole series of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points which should be considered when choosing insurance in order to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The 25-year-olds face numerous obstacles, such as low driving practices and young driving licences, when choosing a low-priced insurance policy.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to complete full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full-box with self-participation, so that the services of a full-payment insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract includes that the customer must pay part of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
The amount is fixed before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain’s main representative at First Europa, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused on its own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hand to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate for the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in the rates stated.
The amount of credit and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can be allowed to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is that with increasing driving practice the accident rate decreases.
It is therefore most appropriate to opt for full insurance with self-employment.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving , explains the Spanish president of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second practical year after the fear of the beginner was put down.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who has no children, it is more advisable to take out full insurance; of course only if it allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and their contributions are therefore also low.
In this case, a full-payment insurance with self-employment (with an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy, which only applies to the third vehicle year, is recommended.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a full-payment insurance with self-employment (with an amount of 150 euros) or an extended insurance policy which only applies to a sufficiently high credit.
Finally, one must note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs, which require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
