In the Philippines, rebel soldiers have given up hiding in a hotel in Manila demanding the overthrow of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
He could not be responsible for bloodshed, said the leader of Antonio Trillanes, who accused the president of corruption and electoral fraud, reporters in the hotel.
Government-faithful soldiers had previously stormed the hotel under tear gas.
